**Abstract:**
Working notes critically examining MacIntyre's "Three Rival Versions of Moral Enquiry" and his interpretation of Aquinas's synthesis of Augustinian and Aristotelian traditions. The author argues MacIntyre confuses "traditions" with "traditions of enquiry" and critiques the conflation of metaphysical accounts with practical understanding of personal identity. Dated October 25, 1992.

